@gateway = http://localhost:8080
@identityServicePath = /identity-service
@projectServicePath = /project-service
@poEmail = po-ismail@example.com
@poPassword = Pass@12345
@inviteeEmail = dev1@example.com
@inviteePassword = Pass@12345
@projectName = Invite Flow Project
@projectDescription = Project used to test invite flow

### 1) Signup PO (run once; may return 400 if already exists)
POST {{gateway}}{{identityServicePath}}/api/v1/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{poEmail}}",
  "password": "{{poPassword}}"
}

### 2) Signup Invitee (run once; may return 400 if already exists)
POST {{gateway}}{{identityServicePath}}/api/v1/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{inviteeEmail}}",
  "password": "{{inviteePassword}}"
}

### 3) Login PO and capture JWT
# @name poLogin
POST {{gateway}}{{identityServicePath}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{poEmail}}",
  "password": "{{poPassword}}"
}

### 4) Login Invitee and capture JWT
# @name inviteeLogin
POST {{gateway}}{{identityServicePath}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{inviteeEmail}}",
  "password": "{{inviteePassword}}"
}

### 5) Create project as PO (PO becomes ACTIVE member)
# @name createProject
POST {{gateway}}{{projectServicePath}}/api/v1/projects/create
Authorization: Bearer {{poLogin.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "{{projectName}}",
  "description": "{{projectDescription}}",
  "state": "ACTIVE"
}

### 6) PO invites user to project as DEV (status starts as PENDING)
POST {{gateway}}{{projectServicePath}}/api/v1/projects/{{createProject.response.body.id}}/invites
Authorization: Bearer {{poLogin.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{inviteeEmail}}",
  "role": "DEV"
}

### 7) Invitee lists my pending invites
# @name myInvites
GET {{gateway}}{{projectServicePath}}/api/v1/projects/invites/me
Authorization: Bearer {{inviteeLogin.response.body.token}}

### 8) Invitee responds ACCEPT
PUT {{gateway}}{{projectServicePath}}/api/v1/projects/{{createProject.response.body.id}}/invites/respond
Authorization: Bearer {{inviteeLogin.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "decision": "ACCEPT"
}

### 9) Optional: Create another project to test REJECT path
# @name createProjectReject
POST {{gateway}}{{projectServicePath}}/api/v1/projects/create
Authorization: Bearer {{poLogin.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "{{projectName}} REJECT",
  "description": "Project used to test reject response",
  "state": "ACTIVE"
}

### 10) Optional: PO invites same user to second project
POST {{gateway}}{{projectServicePath}}/api/v1/projects/{{createProjectReject.response.body.id}}/invites
Authorization: Bearer {{poLogin.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{inviteeEmail}}",
  "role": "SM"
}

### 11) Optional: Invitee responds REJECT on second project
PUT {{gateway}}{{projectServicePath}}/api/v1/projects/{{createProjectReject.response.body.id}}/invites/respond
Authorization: Bearer {{inviteeLogin.response.body.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "decision": "REJECT"
}

### 12) Cleanup: Delete first project as PO
DELETE {{gateway}}{{projectServicePath}}/api/v1/projects/{{createProject.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{poLogin.response.body.token}}

### 13) Cleanup: Delete second project as PO
DELETE {{gateway}}{{projectServicePath}}/api/v1/projects/{{createProjectReject.response.body.id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{poLogin.response.body.token}}
